In /etc/nginx/conf.d/custom_rules.conf, define `upstream api_backend { server 127.0.0.1:3001 max_fails=3 fail_timeout=30s; }`. This ensures Nginx marks the backend as down after 3 failures for 30 seconds.
<info added on 2026-03-07T00:37:13.472Z>
Open the file with nano using sudo nano /etc/nginx/conf.d/custom_rules.conf. Navigate to the client.samixism.com server block. Before the existing location / line, insert the following two blocks without deleting anything:

location /api/ {
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto https;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-SSL on;
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
    client_max_body_size 210m;
    proxy_read_timeout 300s;
    proxy_send_timeout 300s;
    proxy_connect_timeout 60s;
}

location /admin/api/ {
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto https;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-SSL on;
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
}

The existing catch-all block for location / must remain last and unchanged, proxying to http://127.0.0.1:3000. Save in nano using Ctrl+X, Y, then Enter. Order matters: Nginx matches location blocks from most-specific to least, so /api/ and /admin/api/ must appear before location / or they will never be reached. Verify the edit before running nginx by executing sudo grep -n 'location\|proxy_pass\|client_max_body' /etc/nginx/conf.d/custom_rules.conf. The output should show /api/ routing to 3001, /admin/api/ routing to 3001, and / routing to 3000 in that exact order.
</info added on 2026-03-07T00:37:13.472Z>
<info added on 2026-03-07T02:23:05.412Z>
Added /api/ and /admin/api/ location blocks to custom_rules.conf inside the client.samixism.com server block. Created backup custom_rules.conf.bak.pre-api. Nginx syntax check passed and reload was successful. Verified the health endpoint returns HTTP/2 200 via HTTPS and the frontend continues to serve HTTP 200. Confirmed upload directives including 210m body, 300s read/send timeout, and 60s connect timeout are correctly set at lines 66-69.
</info added on 2026-03-07T02:23:05.412Z>
